com.dutinfo.gimeole.ClassesUtiles

Class PolynomialRegression

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.dutinfo.gimeole.ClassesUtiles.PolynomialRegression

  • public class PolynomialRegression
extends java.lang.Object
    Class representing a polynomial regression on the supplied training data. Allows efficient multithreaded computation of optimal polynomial degree for trained data and supplied test data

        public static int getOptimalPolynomialDegreeWithTestData(java.util.List<Point> trainingData,
                                                         java.util.List<Point> testData,
                                                         boolean terminalOutput)
                                                  throws java.lang.InterruptedException
        Multithreaded implementation of a method based on Root Mean Square Error (RMSE) comparison to obtain the optimal polynomial degree that minimises the RMSE error, and therefore improves the accuracy of the trained data, given test data.
        Parameters:
        testData - the data we want to optimise the regression for
        terminalOutput - do you want the thread ids, errors, polynomial degrees and elapsed times to be outputted to the standard output?
        Returns:
        the integer representing the optimal degree for the polynomial regression for the trained data
        Throws:
        java.lang.InterruptedException

      • getOptimalPolynomialDegreeWithTestData

        public static int getOptimalPolynomialDegreeWithTestData(java.util.List<Point> trainingData,
                                                         java.util.List<Point> testData)
                                                  throws java.lang.InterruptedException
        Multithreaded implementation of a method based on Root Mean Square Error (RMSE) comparison to obtain the optimal polynomial degree that minimises the RMSE error, and therefore improves the accuracy of the trained data, given test data. By default, it prints to terminal the errors, polynomial degrees, the thread ids and the elapsed time.
        Parameters:
        testData - the data we want to optimise the regression for
        Returns:
        the integer representing the optimal degree for the polynomial regression for the trained data
        Throws:
        java.lang.InterruptedException

      • getOptimalPolynomialRegression

        public static PolynomialRegression getOptimalPolynomialRegression(java.util.List<Point> trainingData,
                                                                  java.util.List<Point> testData,
                                                                  boolean terminalOutput)
                                                           throws java.lang.InterruptedException
        Returns the optimal polynomial regression (with minimised RMSE) for the supplied training data and test data. Also prints the errors, poly-degrees and time elapsed in the computation. This also includes the thread ids, as this is a multithreaded implementation. Bear in mind, however, that this method is computationally intensive should a lot of testing points be supplied.
        Parameters:
        trainingData - the training data for the regression
        testData - the test data to minimise the RMSE error of
        terminalOutput - do you want the thread ids, errors, polynomial degrees and elapsed times to be outputted to the standard output?
        Returns:
        the optimal Polynomial Regression for the supplied training data and test data
        Throws:
        java.lang.InterruptedException
